Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, worn. Name Aristomachos. From same die as Delos TD2767.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (77)
